WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.000
Before we start, let me ask you a question:

00:00:02.000 --> 00:00:04.316
What's your budget for a tablet?

00:00:04.316 --> 00:00:05.966
Take a look at this new Lenovo tablet.

00:00:05.966 --> 00:00:06.933
It's in the 2,000-yuan price range.

00:00:06.933 --> 00:00:08.099
For an iPad, 

00:00:08.099 --> 00:00:09.750
that wouldn't even cover the starting price.

00:00:09.750 --> 00:00:10.283
But this one

00:00:10.283 --> 00:00:12.366
 really brings something different to the table.

00:00:12.366 --> 00:00:13.416
So let's find out what makes 

00:00:13.416 --> 00:00:15.533
the Lenovo AI Tablet Xiaoxin Pro 13

00:00:15.533 --> 00:00:16.783
 so special.

00:00:27.416 --> 00:00:28.816
After making so many tablets, 

00:00:28.816 --> 00:00:30.383
Lenovo's Xiaoxin line always feels

00:00:30.383 --> 00:00:32.449
 different from other Android tablets to me

00:00:32.449 --> 00:00:33.716
especially its system.

00:00:33.716 --> 00:00:36.116
Maybe because Lenovo started out making Windows PCs,

00:00:36.116 --> 00:00:38.516
its tablets also have a strong Windows vibe.

00:00:38.516 --> 00:00:39.783
Normally, when you connect a keyboard to a tablet,

00:00:39.783 --> 00:00:41.916
you just want to type or do some light work.

00:00:41.916 --> 00:00:42.716
Look at Apple:

00:00:42.716 --> 00:00:44.616
they'd rather put the A18 Pro in MacBook 

00:00:44.616 --> 00:00:47.199
than give iPad a proper desktop interface.

00:00:47.199 --> 00:00:47.933
But Lenovo?

00:00:47.933 --> 00:00:50.083
Plug in the keyboard, and it switches to Infinite Workspace.

00:00:50.083 --> 00:00:50.750
Once you're in, 

00:00:50.750 --> 00:00:51.116
check out 

00:00:51.116 --> 00:00:52.716
the Start bar at the bottomand 

00:00:52.716 --> 00:00:54.316
the desktop layout.

00:00:54.316 --> 00:00:55.983
I won't say it's almost the same as Windows

00:00:55.983 --> 00:00:57.550
it's basically identical.

00:00:57.550 --> 00:00:58.516
When you open apps, 

00:00:58.516 --> 00:01:00.033
they're in 

00:01:00.033 --> 00:01:01.449
Windows-like windows too.

00:01:01.449 --> 00:01:03.316
You can resize and drag them freely, just like on a PC.

00:01:03.316 --> 00:01:05.633
You can even make them tiny.

00:01:05.633 --> 00:01:06.616
When you're in online classes, 

00:01:06.616 --> 00:01:07.616
you can have MOOCs here, 

00:01:07.616 --> 00:01:08.800
notes here, 

00:01:08.800 --> 00:01:10.033
Weibo here, 

00:01:10.033 --> 00:01:12.016
and WeChat ready to chat.

00:01:12.449 --> 00:01:14.550
Now that it's upgraded to 13 inches, 

00:01:14.550 --> 00:01:15.716
the keyboard is also much bigger.

00:01:15.716 --> 00:01:17.650
Typing feels way better 

00:01:17.650 --> 00:01:18.949
than on the 11-inch model.

00:01:19.400 --> 00:01:22.483
This keyboard also has a fun AI key.

00:01:22.483 --> 00:01:23.000
Press it, 

00:01:23.000 --> 00:01:24.416
type what you want

00:01:24.416 --> 00:01:27.599
like a copy for Crazy Thursday

00:01:27.599 --> 00:01:28.483
hit the key again, 

00:01:29.266 --> 00:01:30.449
and it's done instantly.

00:01:30.449 --> 00:01:31.900
Best of all,

00:01:31.900 --> 00:01:33.099
 it works anywhere 

00:01:33.099 --> 00:01:33.933
you can type

00:01:33.933 --> 00:01:35.033
even in games.

00:01:35.750 --> 00:01:37.216
And it's 

00:01:39.500 --> 00:01:41.233
not just the PC mode.

00:01:41.233 --> 00:01:43.366
Lenovo's floating windows are also very PC-like.

00:01:43.366 --> 00:01:44.933
Most other Android tablets 

00:01:44.933 --> 00:01:46.516
only let you run two floating windows at once.

00:01:46.516 --> 00:01:48.533
Lenovo lets you open a bunch.

00:01:48.766 --> 00:01:51.216
The interface might get a little messy,

00:01:51.216 --> 00:01:52.433
but if you want to open them, 

00:01:52.433 --> 00:01:53.599
it lets you.

00:01:53.599 --> 00:01:54.466
It also supports app clones

00:01:54.466 --> 00:01:55.766
up to four.

00:01:55.766 --> 00:01:56.900
Plus the original app, 

00:01:56.900 --> 00:01:57.866
that's five accounts total.

00:01:57.866 --> 00:01:58.633
Really? 

00:01:58.633 --> 00:02:01.433
Does anyone need five accounts for one app?

00:02:02.666 --> 00:02:05.000
This generation's system is all about polishing and adding useful features.

00:02:05.000 --> 00:02:06.699
Now that everyone's connecting with Apple, 

00:02:06.699 --> 00:02:08.233
Lenovo can't fall behind.

00:02:08.233 --> 00:02:10.866
Super Connect lets you share files with iOS.

00:02:10.866 --> 00:02:12.166
Photos from your iPhone 

00:02:12.166 --> 00:02:12.866
can be sent straight to the tablet

00:02:13.466 --> 00:02:14.599
 with one tap.

00:02:14.599 --> 00:02:15.800
Photos I take 

00:02:16.466 --> 00:02:18.000
can be dragged right into PowerPoint.

00:02:18.266 --> 00:02:20.333
Who needs a file transfer app anymore?

00:02:20.650 --> 00:02:22.816
It works with laptops too—even better

00:02:22.816 --> 00:02:23.633
 and easier.

00:02:23.633 --> 00:02:25.016
You don't need a Lenovo laptop;

00:02:25.016 --> 00:02:27.050
 just download the app from Microsoft Store.

00:02:27.050 --> 00:02:27.949
Once connected, 

00:02:27.949 --> 00:02:29.983
there's a file hub on your PC.

00:02:30.183 --> 00:02:30.949
Pictures, 

00:02:32.716 --> 00:02:33.283
files, 

00:02:33.816 --> 00:02:34.583
copied text

00:02:34.583 --> 00:02:36.183
all sync seamlessly.

00:02:36.216 --> 00:02:37.949
You can even stream 

00:02:37.949 --> 00:02:39.116
tablet apps to your PC,

00:02:39.116 --> 00:02:41.316
displaying up to five at the same time.

00:02:41.316 --> 00:02:42.483
With this, 

00:02:42.483 --> 00:02:44.483
why install an Android emulator?

00:02:44.483 --> 00:02:46.616
I've got real Android on my PC.

00:02:47.150 --> 00:02:48.349
But that's not all.

00:02:48.349 --> 00:02:50.816
It can even work as a wireless secondary display for your computer.

00:02:50.816 --> 00:02:53.083
Once connected, it shows up in Windows settings.

00:02:53.083 --> 00:02:55.983
You can drag apps over

00:02:55.983 --> 00:02:57.550
 and control them directly with touch.

00:02:57.550 --> 00:02:58.550
Besides the tablet itself, 

00:02:58.550 --> 00:03:00.816
the stylus for this Xiaoxin model is also updated.

00:03:00.816 --> 00:03:02.183
First, check the back end.

00:03:02.783 --> 00:03:04.949
Yep, flip it around, and it works as an eraser

00:03:04.949 --> 00:03:06.150
super intuitive.

00:03:06.150 --> 00:03:08.150
When you write, different brushes

00:03:08.150 --> 00:03:10.250
 simulate corresponding vibrations and sounds.

00:03:18.116 --> 00:03:19.516
The motor inside the pen 

00:03:19.516 --> 00:03:22.849
even gives the screen a slight paper-like texture.

00:03:23.616 --> 00:03:25.050
It mimics not just pencils, 

00:03:25.050 --> 00:03:26.116
but ballpoint pens too.

00:03:26.116 --> 00:03:27.583
Press down on any screen,

00:03:27.583 --> 00:03:28.516
 the pen vibrates,

00:03:28.516 --> 00:03:30.116
and a small icon pops up.

00:03:30.116 --> 00:03:32.650
Then you can draw or write directly on the screen.

00:03:32.650 --> 00:03:34.050
Tap save, 

00:03:34.050 --> 00:03:36.550
and it becomes an image in your gallery.

00:03:36.583 --> 00:03:38.583
It's just like using a real pen.

00:03:38.583 --> 00:03:39.883
Back in school, 

00:03:39.883 --> 00:03:42.016
I used to click the top of my ballpoint pen nonstop

00:03:42.016 --> 00:03:43.516
